<br>
&quot;Let not the friend misjudge my calm for serenity, my peace for complacency, nor my stillness for apathy. Let not my enemy misjudge my truce for fear, my aide for respect, nor my respect for friendship. My heart burns with Hatred pure and deep, consumed with the brimstone of Innoruuk's kiss. Hatred is the nutrient of my soul, the source of my power and the essence of my being. If I am calm, if I am still, it is because I am one with who I am and one with whom I shall ever be. I am the tool of Hate's desire. That is enough.&quot;<br>
<br>
To know yourself is enough, for in it you shall find the creator. Seek it, know it, accept it; for the power of that knowledge shall set you free.<br>
